reviews.review_text:
great recording! This is one of the best sounding aud tapes from a shed that I've ever heard...this was obviously recorded from outside the taper section, because you cannot hear the boomy echo of the shed itself...this one sounds like it was recorded way over on Jerry's side, with the mics aimed at the big speakers that were hung off of the front of the amphitheater itself for the folks on the hill to enjoy (instead of the side-stage speakers, with all of the attendent crowd noise and boomy echo).

If you like a good AUD tape and are a fan of the summer '92 run (like me), get this one. It Rules with an Iron Boot :-)
